doc.previous: On November 21, 2013, A Dreamlifter operated by Atlas Air Worldwide Holdings, accidentally landed at Col. James Jabara airfield in Kansas, the pilot mistaking that airfield for the McConnell Air Force Base in Wichita, 9 miles south. No one was injured in the incident and the plane departed Jabara airfield the following day, making a successful landing at McConnell.[33]
doc.after: The 747 LCF main cargo compartment has a volume of 65,000 cubic feet (1,840 cubic meters).[34]
